the photo on the right is today, a few weeks before starting prep for my next shows. i’m currently fluctuating between 146-149 lbs. 15 months off to focus on building this physique. whether that’s all muscle growth, I doubt it 😂 but the photos go to show that there has been growth indeed.

do you have to love working out?

although it’s a bonus when you find exercise you enjoy & I definitely advocate to explore that but, NO. not all of you are going to love working out like I do. but you know what? that’s okay. 

I have a client who has HATED working out for 2 years, but guess what? she has continuously showed up for 2 years anyway and has ALWAYS felt better when she’s done 😌

you don’t have to love lifting weights, or cardio, or biking, or swimming, or whatever activity it is that you do. but you NEED to show up for yourself for the soul purpose that you will feel amazing when you do & your health will thank you. discipline over motivation 👏🏼

what’s your favorite type of exercise? 💦 let me know in the comments!

wanna know how to get rid of cellulite sally?

you DON’T 🤷🏽‍♀️ most women have cellulite. the only way to make it seem less apparent is by losing body fat. just like how everyone has ab muscles, but you can’t see them until you lose the body fat on top of them (with some core work of course).

so stop using the creams & gels or whatever else is claiming to get rid of it 🙉 I get it, it might make you insecure but if it weren’t for media portraying it as a negative, no one would care. 

NORMALIZE IT. anyone else feel me here? 🙋🏽‍♀️

what is fitness to you?

fitness is the best investment you could make. it’s not just about looking good, but about feeling good 🙌🏼if there was one thing I want to leave on this planet when i’m gone, it’s the community I aim to build in this. I just want to show how liberating fitness can be to you. if you’re struggling mentally, go release those endorphins. if you’re having health issues, go move. if you’re wanting to escape from reality, go workout & be alone with yourself in a healthy way.

fitness serves ANY & EVERY purpose ❤️

if you’re needing some words of encouragement, my dms are always open. you need this & you can do this. 

what is fitness to you? I want to know 👏🏼

fun fact 👉🏼 I used to have a flat ass & noodle arms

it’s one thing in this world that irks me the most.. people dismissing your hard work & dedication 👊🏼 i’ve been around the block of body types 😂 I wasn’t born out of the womb with just “good genetics.” although that may play a part, it’s the ENVIRONMENT that has the overall effect on your physicality.

people ask me how long it takes to grow a fat a$$ and obtain a certain body type.. 

here’s my response👇🏼
your LIFETIME 🤷🏽‍♀️

it never ends. it’s a constant work in progress. as soon as you realize your health, fitness & nutrition will be a factor in your life FOREVER, the sooner you will see your results 🥰

8 years & counting for me since I started my fitness journey.. how about yours? 🤔

here’s what I mean👇🏼

there’s a difference between pushing yourself to reps until failure & overdoing it with poor form/control. I am NOT saying to push so hard you’re failing every set & possibly injuring yourself.

there’s so many people I see training 3 sets 15 reps barely challenging themselves & wondering why they aren’t progressing in the gym 🙇🏽‍♀️

my piece of advice to anyone training for hypertrophy (muscle growth/fat loss) and/or bodybuilding is to train within 2-3 reps of failure. so if you easily achieve the rep range you’re going for, increase the weight. the last few reps should REALLY SUCK 👏🏼

most people have bad things to say about prepping/cutting, keeping track of your diet, etc.. 

y’all may not notice a huge difference between the two photos, but the left is now and the right is when I was in the middle of a prep 5 months ago. i’ve gained 20 lbs since then.

back then I was lean & physically happy. bounced back & forth between mentally happy & mentally not. today i’m thicker than i’d want be.. yet still bounce back & forth between being physically & mentally happy. sometimes you’re never content. you’ll always want more. you reach one goal, something else gives. the grass is never greener on EITHER side for me. 

but one thing I can say is, I actually felt way better physiologically 5 months ago even being in a cutting phase. I stopped taking my vitamins/minerals, gave up meal prepping/counting macros, only trained 3-4 times per week. I thought I was giving my body a break (and for awhile I may have needed that anyway), but i’ve been feeling like 💩 lol. i’m fatigued, bloated, unhappy, irregular, etc. 

everyone has different experiences with cutting. and of course i’m aware some have detrimental effects to their health. apart from those cases, it seems to be the majority nowadays that people bash on weighing themselves, counting macros, or any other form of accountability. 

maybe i’m the minority in this, but I felt much better with a routine & accountability. i’m still learning what the best balance is for me and am JUST NOW starting to love the body i’m in ❤️
